"when passed to ``datetime.datetime.fromisoformat``.  Can contain time "
"zone offset; see more at description of ``date-time``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/basicproc/zero.rst:973
msgid "date"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/basicproc/zero.rst:971
msgid ""
"Date in ISO format.  See description of `time` for when this is valid. "
"Defaults to ``panel.date.isoformat()`` where ``panel`` is the second "
"argument in ``__init__`` (aside from ``self``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/basicproc/zero.rst:978
msgid "date-time"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/basicproc/zero.rst:976
msgid ""
"Date time in ISO format.  Must be a valid string when passed to "
"``datetime.datetime.fromisoformat``.  Can contain time zone offset which "
"will be preserved as opposed to inheriting from"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/basicproc/zero.rst:980
msgid ""
"Then we have data and input.  These are the primary ways to store data as"
" we discussed in `Data Model and Images`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/basicproc/zero.rst:985
msgid "data"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/basicproc/zero.rst:984
msgid ""
"The text data verbatim.  Or, if ``data-encoding`` is specified, the "
"encoded ASCII string verbatim.  May be a string or a list of strings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/basicproc/zero.rst:995
msgid "input"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/basicproc/zero.rst:988
msgid ""
"The path of the file containing the data.  The program will first seek "
"the path in the current working directory (``os.getcwd()`` or "
"``basicproc.BASE_DIR`` which you can modify for more control) and then "
"``paths`` if you specified them, treating all of them as relative paths "
"to ``BASE_DIR``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/basicproc/zero.rst:994
msgid ""
"Side note: ``paths`` specified in the current panel are sought first, and"
" then ``paths`` specified at the top level are sought second."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/basicproc/zero.rst:1009
msgid "data-encoding"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/basicproc/zero.rst:998
msgid ""
