"By saying \"defaulting to\" after an inference I mean the case when the "
"inference fails.  For inferring from an extension, it would be finding no"
" extension at all or not able to identify the extension (like in the case"
" of ``some.crazyname``).  For inferring from a type or encoding, it would"
" be the case of finding the type or encoding unset.  For the case of "
"type, the type may also be unregistered, causing the lookup to fail."
